# <type>[optional scope]: <description>
#
# [optional body]
#
# [optional footer(s)]

# --- COMMIT END ---
# Type can be:
#   feat     (new feature)
#   fix      (bug fix)
#   docs     (documentation)
#   style    (formatting, no code change)
#   refactor (refactoring code)
#   test     (adding tests)
#   chore    (build/tooling changes)
#   perf     (performance improvements)
#   ci       (CI/CD changes)
#   build    (build system changes)
#   revert   (reverting changes)
#
# Scope can be:
#   api, frontend, backend, core, db, queue, auth, config, deps, docker, ci, docs, tests
#
# Breaking change: Add ! after type/scope or include BREAKING CHANGE: in footer
#
# Examples:
#   feat(api): add user authentication endpoint
#   fix(frontend): resolve modal dialog closing issue
#   feat(api)!: redesign user management API
#   docs: update API documentation
#   chore(deps): update dependencies to latest versions
#
# Remember:
#   - Use imperative mood in subject line
#   - Limit first line to 100 characters
#   - Reference issues and pull requests liberally
#   - Consider if this change requires documentation updates